node.text: Michael Kenneth Williams today too??? A stunning actor, the most believable jazz trumpet player ever on film in Motherless Brooklyn, and one of the greatest characters in a television series EVER IN HISTORY in The Wire. What a loss, I thought we’d get so much more of him. He honored the soul of his characters. So much depth in his words. Rest easy MKW.
